creating a Dockerfile: 
	-Specify a base image
	-run some commands to install additional programs
	-Specify a comand to run on a container startup

Dockerfile commands: 
-adding commands at the end of the list: will used the cache of anything before
-adding a new command on the top of the command list: will not used the cache and building a new image from scratch 

Tagging an image: 
docker build -t <tags the image> <diretory of files/folders> 
-ex: 
docker build -t hlin/redis:latest . 

